ActAppropriation Act No. 2, 2016-17
PrecisAppointment of DONALD BOBIASH as Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of Canada to the Republic of Colombia; IAN BURNEY as Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of Canada to Japan; PERRY CALDERWOOD as High Commissioner for Canada to the Islamic Republic of Pakistan; HEATHER CAMERON as High Commissioner for Canada to the Republic of Ghana; ANTOINE CHEVRIER as High Commissioner for Canada to the Republic of Mozambique; CHRIS COOTER as Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of Canada to the Republic of Turkey, with concurrent accreditation to the Republic of Azerbaijan and to the Republic of Georgia, with residence in Ankara; JENNIFER DAUBENY as Consul General of Canada in Bangalore (Republic of India); LISE FILIATRAULT as Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of Canada to the Republic of Senegal; EMI FURUYA as Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of Canada to the Kingdom of Denmark; KEVIN HAMILTON as Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of Canada to the Republic of Moldova, with residence in Bucharest; CARLA HOGAN RUFELDS as High Commissioner for Canada to the Republic of Trinidad and Tobago; MASUD HUSAIN as Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of Canada to the United Arab Emirates; PING KITNIKONE as Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of Canada to the Socialist Republic of Vietnam; MARIE LEGAULT as High Commissioner for Canada in Barbados, with concurrent accreditation in the Commonwealth of Dominica, the Commonwealth of Grenada, the Commonwealth of Antigua and Barbuda, the Commonwealth of Saint Lucia, the Commonwealth of the Federation of Saint Kitts and Nevis, and the Commonwealth of Saint Vincent and the Grenadines, with residence in Bridgetown; MATTHEW LEVIN as Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of Canada to the Kingdom of Spain, with concurrent accreditation to the Principality of Andorra, with residence in Madrid; DEBORAH LYONS as Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of Canada to the State of Israel; PETER MACDOUGALL as Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of Canada to the Hashemite Kingdom of Jordan; IAN MYLES as High Commissioner for Canada to the United Republic of Tanzania, with concurrent accreditation as Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of Canada to the Union of the Comoros, with residence in Dar-es-Salaam; JEFF NANKIVELL as Consul General of Canada to the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region (People’s Republic of China); OLIVIER NICOLOFF as Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of Canada to the Kingdom of Belgium; DONICA POTTIE as Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of Canada to the Kingdom of Thailand, with concurrent accreditation to the Lao People’s Democratic Republic, with residence in Bangkok; ISABELLE POUPART as Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of Canada to Hungary; BARBARA RICHARDSON as Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of Canada to the Czech Republic; and ULRIC SHANNON as Consul General of Canada in Istanbul (Republic of Turkey).
